  "title": "CARPENTER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Read blueprints, take precise measurements, and cut, shape, and assemble materials to build and install structures such as window frames, doors, staircases, and furniture. Perform inspections, repairs, and maintenance while following safety guidelines and adapting to varied work schedules.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Read blueprints, drawings, and sketches to understand project requirements fully</li><li>Take accurate measurements and calculate material sizes and quantities needed</li><li>Cut, shape, and smooth lumber and other materials (e.g., fiberglass) according to specifications</li><li>Build window frames, doors, staircases, and frame buildings using raw or pre-constructed materials</li><li>Lay out flooring, roofing, or drywall ensuring surfaces are level and properly aligned</li><li>Carve, assemble, and install furniture, cabinets, shelves, and other items at designated locations</li><li>Inspect work sites and perform repairs or maintenance as needed</li><li>Construct scaffolding and other temporary construction structures safely</li><li>Use electrical and manual tools (powered saws, hammers, rulers, etc.) proficiently to complete tasks</li><li>Follow safety guidelines consistently to maintain a safe work environment</li><li>Adapt to work night shifts, Sundays, public holidays, and odd hours based on customer requirements</li><li>Maintain good physical condition and endurance to perform physically demanding tasks</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience working with carpentry materials and techniques</li><li>Ability to read and interpret technical documents and drawings accurately</li><li>Excellent understanding of carpentry installation and construction methods</li></ul>",
